OL,6,FIf you've been affected by any of the
OL,7,Fissues raised in this article, you can
OL,8,Ffind organisations that can offer you
OL,9,Fsupport and advice .
OL,11,FHe was found guilty of sexual assault
OL,12,Fby penetration without consent and was
OL,13,Fjailed for three and a half years.
OL,15,FThe judge read the victim's personal
OL,16,Fstatement which explained how her
OL,17,Fwhole world had been 'torn apart' and
OL,18,Fthat she does not believe any part of
OL,19,FBraun is sorry for what he did to her.
